Body:
Hi George, 

Can you please send someone out to fix our oven. It has stopped working. It does not produce heat. The fan still works and so does the grill. But no heat when on the oven setting. 

Thank you 
Rachel

Sent from my iPhone

Hi George 

On a separate note, how much notice does the selling agent have to give us to hold a showing to prospective buyers? 

The selling agent is aggressively pushing us for an open this Saturday. We've put our foot down and have said no unless it's after 3pm on Saturday but I just want to make sure we are acting reasonably. 

Thanks 

Tara

Subject: URGENT - Unit 22 1-13 Russell st baulkham hills - mould issue uncovered

Hi George 

This is absolutely the worst timing for this, however we've uncovered a mould problem in our sons bedroom. 

We were beginning to tidy up in preparation for the selling agent's photographer and we moved a bookshelf and have uncovered a pretty severe mould issue on the carpet. Please see photo attached. 

I called a carpet cleaning business (LTM Carpet Cleaning - https://maps.app.goo.gl/omFBc8CrBh6thcPg9) and he's indicated the carpet will need to be removed and replaced. He suggested cutting out the mould and patching it with a piece of carpet from inside the built in wardrobe if the landlord has just have any carpet off cuts. 

Lee from the carpet cleaning business said its also possible that the mould and moisture came from underneath the carpet (possibly an issue with the building and water getting into places during periods of heavy rain). We are aware that this bedroom sits on top of our neighbour's garage (unit 21) and during periods of heavy rain, the back wall of her garage is often wet and leaking water. The whole basement seems to leak in lots of places when it rains heavily. 

At this point I'm not sure if it's an issue for strata or an issue we need to be responsible for (I acknowledge the placement is also right next to the door so it's possible that rain got in and just seeped under the book case), however there is no mould ANYWHERE else in the room besides under the book case (I.e. not even closer to the door that would have gotten more water if rain got in).

I have to work tomorrow morning so I will call you sometime between 11-12 to discuss how we go about quickly removing the mouldy patch, fixing the carpet and working out who is responsible. 

We have covered up the mould patch with old linen to prevent mould spores from travelling (as suggested by the carpet guy), have sectioned off the room and have moved our son out of the room for now. 

Can you communicate with the landlord about whether they have carpet offcuts stored somewhere and if they want to halt the sale process of the property as well? Joven and I are also away (overseas and interstate between 11 June to 19 June - we let the selling agent know this as well but haven't notified them of the current mould issue). 

Sorry to drop this on you at the start of your working week. We'll chat tomorrow and go from there. 

Kind regards

Tara and Joven 

-- 

- Joven Demonteverde
